      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Carbon dioxide (CO₂) plays a significant role in polluting the air around us. When CO₂ reaches the atmosphere, it combines with water molecules to form carbonic acid, which contributes to acid rain. Acid rain can damage vegetation by killing plants that cannot withstand the acidity of the rainwater. This process reduces the amount of oxygen available in the air for life on Earth. Additionally, CO₂ is a greenhouse gas, leading to further warming of the Earth's surface and atmosphere, exacerbating the effects of climate change.",
        "state": "done"
      }
