      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Embedding models refers to techniques where a computer program is integrated into another system or platform. This integration allows for seamless interaction and data flow between them. Think of it as connecting two separate pieces of software so they work together hand in hand.\n\nImagine a web browser alongside your favorite app. When you open the app, it can access the internet to display its interface. That's embedding an app into your computer.\n\nBut embedding models is more complex than that. It's not just about bringing two things together; it's about ensuring that all components work perfectly with each other. This tight integration helps in delivering a better overall experience for users.\n\nIt’s like how different parts of a machine come together to create smooth operation. Whether it's handling data, performing tasks, or providing information, the way models are embedded ensures everything works at its best.",
        "state": "done"
      }
